The tenth album from Red Hot Chili Peppers guitarist John Frusciante is more psychedelic than his previous releases, and features guest appearances from Johnny Marr and Frusciante's bandmate Flea. 'The Empyrean' is a concept album following a single story throughout, and contains a cover of Tim Buckley's 'Song To The Siren'. It is Frusciante's first solo release in four years and his first since the Chili Peppers went on 'indefinite hiatus'.
